; binding-depth-band.fk — proof that a single scope with many sequential lets
; resolves correctly: 140 chained bindings, all live at once, each reading the
; previous. Guards the parser binding stack (fk_bd_*, raised 128->1024 on
; 2026-07-02). Under the old 128-slot cap, bindings past 128 were SILENTLY
; dropped (fk_bd_push's `if (fk_bd_top < 128)` no-else) — v128..v139 would fail
; to resolve and the deep value would be wrong, with no witness. This is the
; regression that would have caught that silence; it also proves the fkwu seed
; now agrees with all three walkers on a deep scope.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk
; run: cat form/form-stdlib/core.fk form/form-stdlib/tests/binding-depth-band.fk > /tmp/bd.fk ; ./fkwu --src /tmp/bd.fk  -> 140
;
; Verdict 140 (the deep value v0+139) when the deep scope resolves; 0 otherwise.

(do
    (defn bd-deep ()
        (do
            (let v0 1)
            (let v1 (add v0 1))
            (let v2 (add v1 1))
            (let v3 (add v2 1))
            (let v4 (add v3 1))
            (let v5 (add v4 1))
            (let v6 (add v5 1))
            (let v7 (add v6 1))
            (let v8 (add v7 1))
            (let v9 (add v8 1))
